1 (ii) “Pet” does not include livestock.
2 (b) (1) A person who tortiously causes an injury to or death of a pet while
3 acting individually or through an animal under the person’s ownership, direction, or control
4 is liable to the owner of the pet for compensatory damages.
5 (2) The damages awarded under paragraph (1) of this subsection may not
6 exceed [$10,000] $25,000.
7 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
8 October 1, 2025.

